0033>11:58:07 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: It's not that hard - part I (Assisting)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I forgot to mention my fave way to let a chanter having problems get a chance to get a stun off so they can mezz... <br>
<br>
Run up next to the enchanter and chain-cast chloroblast or your equivalent heal on them.  Chanter's hp goes up which is good, and I have yet to see a case in which more than 2 mobs are still on the chanter after I get 2 chloroblasts off.  You want to be next to the chanter to do this because the chanter will most likely be trying to aoe stun or aoe mezz the mobs to have a little time to get the real mez on them, so you don't want to cast from across the room and break up the grouping.  <br>
<br>
-fel</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaellanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laellanna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Cyber Pimp</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12:34:10 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: It's not that hard - part I (Assisting)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Periodically, I take over mezzing for an enchanter, particularly if I see them being beaten up.  When this happens, often there is miscommunication, as chanter mezz won't overwrite bardic mezz.  When this happens, I entreat upon the enchanters to please let the bard continue mezzing or let the bard know when to drop mez.<br>
<br>
As a side note, when a bard is mezzing, any MR debuff WILL break bardic mezz (as bardic mezz has a MR debuff associated with it).  Please don't use those spells or warn the bard that you're using Tash/Malo/etc.. prior to casting it.  Confuses the heck out of us sometimes when you miss the message in battle spam.<br>
<br>
Laellanna - Bardess of the 59th Tweet<br>
Daena - Clericess of the 59th Bandage</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>I live here.... get out.</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>2:30:32 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: It's not that hard - part I (Assisting)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Yeah, it ain't fun to be bitched at for helping out. I tend to snare every mob I see, and though snare does not break mez, I have been bitched at for doing it. Well ok, i'll just let you die next time if thats what you want, but I would really prefer the enchanters to stay alive. Enchanters I group with seem to be quite happy about not taking the hits, once they get used to it. I frankly consider everytime a caster gets hit to be a mistake on my part, for though I am usally no the main tank, I am damn well a better tank that a robe wearing caster lol. And I can always get rid of the attention I draw upon me once the main tank gets around to engaging that mob.<br>
<br>
When standing next to a mob, it is pretty easy to see if a tank is attacking or just taunting. With double attack/haste and maybe dual wield, swings come so fast when attacking that it really can't be confused with the occasional riposte. And since a riposte only happens when you're getting swung at, it is unlikely to ever break a mez. As mezzed mobs won't be taking those swings.<br>
<br>
Also, on raids with only one enchanter, rooting is a perfectly viable means of helping out. Yes, ranger root breaks mez, but not if you root one of the mobs that are as yet unmezzed. Works like a charm, and it is in fact quite possible for one person to control up to 3 mobs with the use of root alone (in most cases). And though enchanters are indeed able to channel through alot of hits, most mobs have the ability to bash at the most inconvenient times. I know I sometimes get interrupted even with my lvl 15 root, and hybrids have higher channelling than pure casters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think the reason many enchanters prefer to do their job unaided is, that some people tend to mess up big time and they have trouble telling those from the people who are actually helping. It is a problem, and I can understand that unless you know the person standing next to that mob you are trying to mezz, you can get worried that he's one of the jerks that is about to mess up. So if you're worried I don't mind getting that angry tell, as long as you don't mind me telling you back that I am helping rather than causing trouble. <br>
Because no, I am not going to hit a mezzed mob. No, I am not going to use flame lick to draw it onto me. No, I am not going to root it after you mezz it. No, I am not going to get you killed. But yes, I damn well am going to do my best to keep you alive while you do your job. Because that, is -my- job.<br>
<br>
Cheers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
55th outrider of Tunare <BR>
Leader, Avatars of Night<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucalbegath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calbegath</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8:17:50 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: It's not that hard - part I (Assisting)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">/cheer Aaramis<br>
<br>
Nice post.  Two wee comments:<br>
<br>
1.  The above also applies ta groups without an enchanter, where someone else (fer instance a cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) is handling crowd-control duties.<br>
<br>
2.  I doubt this is news, but I discovered this neat trick by accident:  if ye want ta assist without breaking mez, especially in close quarters, assist while sitting.  This'll set the target, and ye'll also get an &quot;Auto attack off.&quot; message, so ye can stand and prepare ta melee or cast without aggroing the mob.<br>
<br>
</font><P>Cheers,<br>
